
/*******************************************************************************
	Documentation Structure
*******************************************************************************/
A document would be an incant field (with a document attribute implied or explicit?) containing some or all of the following members sketched out below in incant field form

    description="some short descriptive title" title;
    contents="a list of the sections within";
    purpose="
        text describing purpose goes here.
        note that incant quotes can span multiple lines";
    tasks has a list of individual tasks like
        task="multi line text can go here" status;
    concerns is like tasks but contains a list of
        concern="short text describing a worry that may not surface
            but maybe it will so watch for it.";
    issues is like concerns but each issue describes a well defined problem
    Sections contains a list of sections (like chapters but may be real short)
        each section follows the form for a document outlined above, but containing only the outline bits that seem relevant

The fields that define a document are not mandatory. So if there are no concerns just leave it out
And any name can be used for members, not just description,contents,purpose ...

